------------------------------------------------
-Borrow service
(Authorization needed for all APIs. Students can create and view their own requests; STAFF/ADMIN can view all and approve/return.)

1. Create borrow request: POST http://localhost:8083/equipment-service/api/borrow/request
Headers:
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN-...
(DONE BY STUDENT)
request:
{
"equipment": { "id": 1 },
"quantityRequested": 2,
"fromDate": "2025-11-05T09:00:00",
"toDate": "2025-11-06T17:00:00"
}

Possible validation responses (status 210):
- "Please enter a valid quantity"
- "<Equipment Name> is invalid"
- "<Equipment Name> is not available"

success response (status 200):

{
"id": 4,
"requester": {
"id": 5,
"name": "Ameya Dikshit",
"email": "ameya@bits.com",
"password": "ameya123",
"role": "STUDENT"
},
"equipment": {
"id": 1,
"name": "Laptop Dell Latitude",
"category": "Electronics",
"conditionDescription": "Good condition, suitable for programming",
"quantity": 10,
"availableQuantity": 10
},
"quantityRequested": 2,
"fromDate": "2025-11-05T09:00:00",
"toDate": "2025-11-06T17:00:00",
"status": "PENDING"
}

2. List borrow requests: GET http://localhost:8083/equipment-service/api/borrow
Headers:
Authorization: Bearer TOKEN-...
(DONE BY STUDENT)

Behavior:
- Student token: returns only that student's requests
- Staff/Admin token: returns all requests

response (example):
[
{
"id": 4,
